      "span_text": "In patient-derived neurons from idiopathic autism, evidence has been found for disturbances in synaptic connectivity and function, with changes in expression of ASD-associated genes, including voltage-gated ion channels. Through use of patient-derived neurons with specific molecular deficits, investigators can identify targeted therapeutic hypotheses."
